title: For Sale:  Brno Mannalicher style Sporterized Mauser 98
postcontent:
Attention Mauser Collectors grab this rare model while you can. This gun is in 98% condition and is a great example of a classic time period in Firearms history. Info below from this year's Blue Book. 
Mauser 98 style action, 23.6 in. barrel with iron sights, checkered walnut stock with Bavarian cheekpiece,  and forearms,  Double set trigger, 7 1/4 lbs.  
This model is historically significant as it was the last center fire bolt action rifle assembled in the famous Brno factory. Guns were built on refurbished military M98 actions from various makers, sourced primarily from the former Yugoslavia.
Configuration was small ring Mauser 98 receiver with double set trigger(s), butterknife bolt, checkered walnut pistol grip stock (half or full length), with cheekpiece and sling swivels.  For more info or to see this great rifle call or text Shooting Starr Sports at 904-Six One Six - 1498.

title: For Sale:  Shooting Range Membership
location: Highlands Ranch, Lone Tree, Southglenn, Denver, Colorado
postcontent:
We are in the planning phases of opening a Shooting Range / Gun Club in the Highlands Ranch / Lone Tree area. We are currently looking for prospective members. 

The range will include a ProShop, Gun Smithing, Child Care, Education and Training, and a Country Club Style lounge for Platinum level members. The plans are currently calling for 5 ranges, 10 lanes each. 4 - 25M Pistol Ranges and 1 - 50M Tactical Rifle Range.

Three membership levels:
Brass, Platinum, and Founding Member. There are an unlimited number of Brass memberships available and a limited number of Platinum and Founding memberships.

Brass Membership has a $300 initiation fee and will have a $30 a month dues.
Benefits include: No range fees, Schedule up to 10 days in advance up to two hours a day range time, one hour free hand gun rental per year (excludes NFA; you cover the ammo), complementary firearms safety check each year, 10 guest passes per year, FFL transfer fee of $15 (normally $30; excluding NFA), members only sales, members only discounts, members only product offerings, discounted range ammo, members only events and leagues, free membership t-shirt, complementary access to child care center while on the range. 

Brass + membership has an initiation fee of $400, monthly dues of $40 includes all of the benefits of the Brass membership but includes the members spouse in the plan.

Brass + Family membership has an initiation fee of $500, monthly dues of $50 includes all of the benefits of the Brass + membership and includes all dependents of the member under the age of 18, and free drop in Range Child Care while on the range.

Platinum membership has an initiation fee of $10,500, monthly dues of $200. Membership level includes all benefits of the Brass + Family membership plus Platinum Lounge, Access to Platinum Shooting Lanes, priority access standard range, 10 guest passes per year (allows guest access to all Platinum lounge amenities), Cost plus pricing on all Pro Shop Non-Firearm items, 1 Firearm purchase at cost per year, Free paper targets, complementary use of all rental firearms (you just cover the ammo), free use of conference room (subject to availability, reservation required), firearm valet, discounted gunsmithing, discounted training, schedule range time 14 days in advance (limit 2 hours a day). This membership level can be sold to members on the waiting list, with transfer fee to be paid to the club of $300. 

Founding Membership has an initiation fee if $20,500, monthly dues of $200. Membership level includes all benefits of the Platinum membership plus  4 guest passes per month (allows guest access to all Platinum lounge amenities), 1 firearm purchase at cost every 6 months, 50% discount on all classes, schedule range time up to 30 days in advance (limit 2 hours a day), membership referral bonuses applied as pro shop credit or towards monthly dues, founding membership is willable, your name on the founding members wall. 

Military and Law Enforcement, two levels exist, Pew Pew Pew and Shenanigans, both are at the Brass Membership levels and include a $100 discount on membership initiation fees and $10 off the monthly membership fees.   Military Active duty (USCG, USN, USAF, USA, USMC), Reserve, Retired, or honorably discharged. Law Enforcement, current or retired. 

All membership levels can pay monthly dues in advance, pay for the entire year and get two months free, it's our happy holidays to you. 

Don't shoot enough to justify a membership but would like to see the club open? Help us out and we will help you out. We are pre-selling range passes - Pistol Range Time for non members is typically $20 an hour per person. We are selling range passes (1hr for one person) at $15 each.  We are selling a limited number of these passes. 

Please email me for more details.

Employees - Currently search for a few good men and women. RSOs and instructors needed NRA certification not necessary but it helps. Sales persons (Current FFL or be able to pass the background check), Gunsmiths, and we need a Chef... 
please send me an email and tell me a little bit about yourself.
